name: ᴛʜᴇ ᴇɪɢʜᴛᴇᴇɴᴛʜ ᴏɴᴇ
description:
This chemigram is a culmination of my interests, skills and styles. The Roman bust is plate 49 of the Charles Bargue book desgined for sight-size drawing. This drawing was originally completed in graphite (by sight-size) and then later transferred to Ilford photographic paper. The bust was blocked in with a glue resist and then developed and fixed with darkroom chemicals.

8K
